    "messageBody": "<div id=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><html><head></head>Kevin,<div class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><br class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"></div><div class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\">I can understand you not wanting to require JDK 8. If I am not mistaken, you can support Java 8 classes but keep compatibility with Java 6 if you use JDK 8 to compile the code with JDK 6 as the target. This is from Oliver Gierke’s comment in Stefan’s link here&nbsp;<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://github.com/hamcrest/JavaHamcrest/issues/82#issuecomment-101392293\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\">https://github.com/hamcrest/JavaHamcrest/issues/82#issuecomment-101392293</a>.</div><div class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><br class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"></div><div class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\">Best,</div><div class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\">Mark</div><div class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><br class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"></div><div class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><br class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><div><blockquote><span title=\"qreply\"> <blockquote type=\"cite\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><div class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\">On Oct 4, 2015, at 7:04 PM, Kevin Cooney ☕ <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:kcooney@...\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\">kcooney@...</a> [junit] &lt;<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:junit@yahoogroups.com\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\">junit@yahoogroups.com</a>&gt; wrote:</div><br class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106Apple-interchange-newline\"><div class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><div id=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106ygrp-mlmsg\" style=\"font-size:13px;font-family:Arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><div id=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106ygrp-msg\" style=\"line-height:1.22em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><div id=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106ygrp-text\" style=\"line-height:1.22em;font-family:Georgia;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><div style=\"line-height:1.22em;margin:0px 0px 1em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><br class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106webkit-block-placeholder\"></div><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.22em;margin:0px 0px 1em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\">JUnit depends on JDK5. The next major version will likely require JDK6. We don&#39;t want to require JDK8.</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.22em;margin:0px 0px 1em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\">Have you looked at Truth?</p><div class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106gmail_quote\" style=\"line-height:1.22em;\">On Oct 4, 2015 11:39 AM, &quot;Mark Silvis<span class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:masilvis22@...\" style=\"line-height:1.22em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\">masilvis22@...</a><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span>[junit]&quot; &lt;<a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:junit@yahoogroups.com\" style=\"line-height:1.22em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\">junit@yahoogroups.com</a>&gt; wrote:<br style=\"line-height:1.22em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><blockquote class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106gmail_quote\" style=\"margin:0px 0px 0px 4px;line-height:1.22em;border-left-width:1px;border-left-color:rgb(204, 204, 204);border-left-style:solid;\"><u style=\"line-height:1.22em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"></u><div style=\"line-height:1.22em;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><span style=\"line-height:1.22em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\">&nbsp;</span><div style=\"line-height:1.22em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><div style=\"line-height:1.22em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><div style=\"line-height:1.22em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><p style=\"line-height:1.22em;margin:0px 0px 1em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\">I would like to contribute to JUnit, and I think I have a good idea for a feature. I’ve found that it would be nice to have assertions that explicitly supported Java 8’s Optional class. I’m thinking something along the lines of assertEmpty() and assertPresent(). Would such an addition be welcomed?<br style=\"line-height:1.22em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><br style=\"line-height:1.22em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\">Thanks,<br style=\"line-height:1.22em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\">Mark<br style=\"line-height:1.22em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"></p></div><div style=\"line-height:1.22em;color:rgb(255, 255, 255);min-height:0px;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"></div></div></div></div></blockquote></div><div style=\"line-height:1.22em;margin:0px 0px 1em;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"><br class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106webkit-block-placeholder\"></div></div><div style=\"line-height:1.22em;color:rgb(255, 255, 255);height:0px;\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"></div></div></div></div></blockquote></span></blockquote></div><br class=\"ygrps-yiv-2101632106\"></div></html></div>", 
